  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_6' aria-label=\" Neha Chandrakant Shroff & Anr. versus The State of Maharashtra & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('6','2025','2025_5_616_626','2025INSC484'); ><font size='4'> <strong>NEHA CHANDRAKANT SHROFF & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF MAHARASHTRA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 616</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 484</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001762025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the order passed by the High Court, rejecting the writ petition filed by the appellants u/Article 226 of the Constitution praying for the possession of property given for temporary occupation to police officials in 1940. Headnotes&dagger; Constitution Art.226 &ndash; Writ jurisdiction &ndash; Exercise of, when alternative remedy available &ndash; Writ petition by the appellant seeking for possession of their two flats which were permitted to be temporarily occupied by the police department at their request to meet the requirement of housing<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 07-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5098/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','2025_5_616_626','2025INSC484','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open